{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17642405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17642405"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:39:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:39:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17939"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17939","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17939"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.4,0.08,0.16,0.28,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10653"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108316"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10653","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10653"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17939"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90719"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4904"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7243"},{"type":"tags","id":"7258"},{"type":"tags","id":"7573"},{"type":"tags","id":"11236"},{"type":"tags","id":"11240"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24818"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24821"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108316","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108316"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for a routine check-up. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDuring the consultation, she expresses interest in learning more about human anatomy, particularly the structure of the skull. You decide to explain the components of the cranial base to her.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following bones does not make up the cranial base?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Parietal","Sphenoid","Temporal","Ethmoid","Occipital"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe cranial base, also known as the base of skull, is formed by several bones that support the brain and form the floor of the cranial cavity. These bones include the \u003Cstrong\u003Esphenoid\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Etemporal\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eethmoid\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003Eoccipital\u003C/strong\u003E bones. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eparietal\u003C/strong\u003E bone, however, is part of the cranial vault, which forms the sides and roof of the cranial cavity, not the base.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esphenoid\u003C/strong\u003E bone is a complex bone located at the base of the skull, contributing to the cranial base and housing the pituitary gland in the sella turcica.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etemporal\u003C/strong\u003E bones are located on the sides of the skull and contribute to the cranial base, housing structures of the ear and forming part of the temporomandibular joint.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eethmoid\u003C/strong\u003E bone is a small, spongy bone located between the eyes, contributing to the cranial base and forming part of the nasal cavity and the orbits.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eoccipital\u003C/strong\u003E bone forms the posterior part of the cranial base and contains the foramen magnum, through which the spinal cord passes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The cranial base is formed by the ethmoid, sphenoid, temporal, and occipital bones.","The parietal bone is part of the cranial vault, not the cranial base."],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume 